## [1.4.0] - 2026-04-28

### v1.4.0 Added

- Completion chime via Web Audio API (`playChime(isWorkEnd)`) — no audio files required. Work sessions end with an ascending 4-note major arpeggio (C5→E5→G5→C6); breaks end with two softer descending tones. Each note uses a quick linear attack and exponential decay for a natural sound.
- Browser notification support (`sendNotification(title, body)`) using the Notifications API. Fires even when the tab is in the background; notifications auto-close after 8 seconds.
- `requestNotificationPermission()` called on boot — prompts the user once if permission is `"default"`, does nothing if already granted or denied.
- Sound and notification toggle buttons ("Sound" / "Notify") in the timer card, styled as pill-shaped toggles that highlight green when active.
- `toggleSound()` and `toggleNotif()` functions — flip preferences, persist state to `localStorage`, and sync button visuals. Enabling sound plays an immediate preview chime.
- `syncSoundToggle()` and `syncNotifToggle()` functions keep button state consistent with both user preference and actual browser permission. Notification button dims with reduced opacity if browser permission was permanently denied.
- `AudioContext` created lazily on first use to comply with browser autoplay policies.

### v1.4.0 Changed

- `onPhaseEnd()` now calls `playChime()` and `sendNotification()` at the start of each phase transition before logging the session.
- Alert preferences default to enabled and survive page reloads via `localStorage` (`pomo_sound`, `pomo_notif` keys).

---

## [1.3.0] - 2026-04-28

### v1.3.0 Changed

- Replaced `setInterval`-based countdown with wall-clock anchoring using `deadlineAt` (`Date.now()` timestamp of phase end), making drift structurally impossible.
- Replaced the `setInterval` render loop with a `requestAnimationFrame` loop (`rafTick`) for smooth, browser-native display updates at the display's refresh rate.
- Pause now snapshots remaining milliseconds (`pausedMsLeft`); resume shifts `deadlineAt` forward by that exact amount so no time is lost or gained.

### v1.3.0 Added

- Page Visibility API integration: `visibilitychange` listener calls `onVisible()` when the tab regains focus, immediately resyncing the display from wall-clock time and restarting the rAF loop.
- `sessionFired` guard flag to ensure a completed session is logged exactly once even if the tab was hidden when the timer expired.

### v1.3.0 Removed

- `timerInterval` state variable and all `setInterval` / `clearInterval` calls.

---

## [1.2.0] - 2026-04-27

### v1.2.0 Added

- Free-text category input (`<input>` + `<datalist>`) replacing the fixed `<select>`, allowing any custom category to be entered (e.g. "Music", "Side project").
- Default suggestions datalist pre-populated with: Work, Learning, Health, Personal, Finance, Creative, Other.
- `catBadge()` function that maps known categories to badge colours and deterministically assigns a colour to unknown ones via a string hash.
- `catDisplay()` function that title-cases stored category strings for display.
- `refreshCatSuggestions()` function that merges goals in memory with `/api/categories` results to keep the datalist up to date across page reloads.
- `/api/categories` endpoint (`GET`) returning all distinct categories currently stored in the database, sorted alphabetically.

### v1.2.0 Changed

- `addGoal()` now reads the category text input instead of a select value, defaulting to "Other" if left blank.
- `loadGoals()` now calls `refreshCatSuggestions()` after every fetch so newly created categories appear as suggestions immediately.
- Removed hardcoded `catColors` and `catLabel` maps from `app.js`.

---

## [1.1.0] - 2026-04-27

### v1.1.0 Added

- Sub-goals support: each goal can have any number of sub-goals with a `status` of `pending`, `done`, or `failed`.
- Sub-goals panel per goal card (expand/collapse via ▼/▲ toggle showing sub-goal count).
- Inline sub-goal entry (type and press Enter or click Add).
- Done / Missed buttons per sub-goal; clicking the active status toggles it back to pending.
- Sub-goal progress summary on each goal card (e.g. "2/3 done · 1 missed").
- Pending sub-goals preview in the Pomodoro tab when a goal with open sub-goals is selected.
- Sub-goal completion rate stat (% done of all tracked sub-goals) on the Log tab.
- Done/Missed badge counts per goal on the Log tab time-by-goal bars.
- `POST /api/goals/<id>/subgoals` — create a sub-goal.
- `PATCH /api/subgoals/<id>` — update sub-goal status.
- `DELETE /api/subgoals/<id>` — delete a sub-goal.
- `subgoals` table in SQLite with `ON DELETE CASCADE` from `goals`.

---

## [1.0.0] - 2026-04-14

### v1.0.0 Added

- Initial release of **pomodoro_app**.
- Flask + SQLite backend with REST API (`goals`, `sessions`, `stats` endpoints).
- Goals management: create, complete (checkbox), and delete goals with title, category, and optional description.
- Pomodoro timer with configurable work and break durations.
- Start, pause/resume, and reset controls.
- Per-goal session logging: completed pomodoros are saved to the database with timestamp.
- Log tab with total pomodoros, total focus time, per-goal time bars, and full session history.
- Dark mode support via `prefers-color-scheme` CSS media query.
- Auto-creation of `pomodoro.db` on first run via `init_db()`.

